data.name: AD Sports TV - JiuJitsu
data.description:
In a collaboration with Obeida Sidani, Executive Creative Director at Les Folies Design Haus, Director and Creative Director Anders Schroder at Frame created these jaw-dropping idents for the Abu Dhabi sports channel AD Sports TV relaunch.

Being fascinated by the HDR look typically associated with commercial sports photography, Anders suggested to re-create this look BUT in live action.  He wanted to achieve a look that was almost synthetic and videogame-like with extreme angles and razor sharp infinite focus but all achieved in-camera. A look that would be synonymous with high performance rather than the performers themselves.

The technique is based on the idea of shooting with multiple exposures and then combine them in post. Furthermore, Anders wanted to shoot high-speed with zero motion blur and considering this was a night shoot which added tremendously to the difficulty.

The team at Frame creative directed, conceptualized and animated the transforming floors under the athlete and the particle systems around him.

Production company was Dubai based VIP Films.

user.name: Jaron Padello
user.bio:
I am a freelance video engineer, digital imaging technician (DIT), and assistant cameraman. 

As an artist & filmmaker my focus is to develop a new voice for the martial art genre and create a visual dialogue of poetic movement, realism, and philosophy within my films. I am currently working on a documentary short called, "Broken Rhythm: The Rudiments of Martial Arts".

Also check out the link above which is also in my Instagram Bio to discover more of @henryakinsbjj "Hidden Jiujitsu" Today Henry is the closet thing to Ricksom Gracie who he achieved his Black Belt from and was also his top student. He still carries the knowledge and more subtle detains that you won't find anywhere else! I've personally trained and been to a seminar with @henryakinsbjj and by far he is the best professor I have come across. His mount, side control and posture are another level I have never felt. He's only 155lb? But when he's on top he feels like 400lb with his weight distribution and pressure! Learn from the best by following the link. I'll be uploading a number of short videos on Henry starting from tomorrow and the next few weeks. Sorry for the last couple techniques that were uploaded! The sound doesn't come out and they were not filmed by myself and I could find out what the problem was? But look out for more footage of the living legend @henryakinsbjj on my YouTube channel #stuartcooperfilms #henryakins #henryakinshiddenjiujitsu #henryAkinsBJJ #hiddenjiujitsu #RicksonGracie #XGuardBrand @xguard

user.name: Stuart Cooper
user.bio: www.stuartcooperfilms.com is dedicated to bringing you the most new and interesting stylish JiuJitsu films on the net and soon DVD. Stuarts aim is to make documentaries on the most accomplished grapplers and MMA fighters in the world so you can sit back, watch, listen and learn from the best in the sport. Stuart is a Brown Belt in JiuJitsu and has been training and competing in the sport for years. But since several accidents have occurred the sport has led him on a new path in making JiuJitsu documentaries as he loves the sort so much and wants to share with people how the sport can change lives for the better. Stuart has now travelled the world and made documentaries with legends of the sport and all the new breed of athletes coming up through the ranks.
